Liverpool’s Gerrard to Return After 7-Month Layoff, Mirror Says: Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-09-16T10:50:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/liverpool-s-gerrard-to-return-after-7-month-layoff-mirror-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
Web.  Gerrard Return  Liverpool captain  Steven Gerrard  could make his comeback
next week after a seven-month injury layoff, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  Gerrard may be on the substitutes’ bench at Tottenham in
two days before playing at Brighton in the Carling Cup on Sept.
21, the Mirror said.  Malouda Bid  Bayern Munich will bid for Chelsea’s Florent Malouda in the
January transfer window,  The Sun  reported.  Malouda, 31, may be available after the Blues signed  Juan Mata , who’s also a winger, the Sun said.  Arsenal Loanee  Arsenal may make Yossi Benayoun’s loan deal permanent,  the
Independent  reported.  The midfielder joined from Chelsea, one of five signings by
the Gunners in the week before the transfer window closed on
Aug. 31, the Independent said.  Ferguson’s ‘Agony’  Manchester United coach  Alex Ferguson  says it’s “agony”
having so many strikers to choose from when he picks the team,
the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Ferguson hasn’t given a start this season to Dimitar Berbatov,  Michael Owen , Federico Macheda and Mame Biram Diouf,
the Mirror said.  Missing Balls  Wigan’s practice was disrupted yesterday after someone took
about 50 of the club’s soccer balls, the Daily Mirror said.  Four of the five ball bags were taken from the training
ground, forcing Roberto Martinez to send the team on a run, the
newspaper said. Police were called to investigate, the Mirror
said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
